## Design Objectives:
* This design is made to be manufactured using a 3-axis CNC carving machine(can be 3D printed)
* The back plate was designed to hold these hardware parts:
    - Potentiometer*3
    - Switch*2
    - Strip LED(will be sticked on the surface)
    - Arduino Uno
    - Self-made transistor PCB
* The holder parts are designed to hold the back-front plate assembly in place(apx 45 degrees)
* Both of the plates (back and front) has screw holes to allow them to be assembled
* No ready text type is used in the BBR text applied on the front plate, the text is manuelly modeled.
* One of the biggest constraints at this design was the dimensions of the CNC workspace

## Software Used:
* The design of this project is mainly done in Autodesk Fusion 360.

## Part List
* HDF wood plates with 4 mm thickness will be used.
* It is suggested to use small(1-1.5 mm) CNC bits for a better result.
* For the assembly of the main two plates m4 screws will be used.
